<div class="container-fluid home-body">
	<div class="row">
			<div class="col-md-6 col-md-offset-3 panel-default">
        <h1 class="margin-base-vertical home-text">Where's the party?</h1>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-lg-7">

            <%= form_tag(search_path, :method => "get", class: "navbar-form navbar-left", id: "search-form") do %>
              <div><%= text_field_tag :search, nil, class: 'form-control', value: current_city %>
              <%= submit_tag 'Go!', class: 'btn btn-warning'%>
            <% end %>
							<a href='#', class='btn btn-primary', data-toggle='modal', data-target='#myScript'>Huh?</a></div>
          </div><!-- /.col-lg-6 -->
        </div><!-- /.row -->
      </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="modal fade" id="myScript" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="myModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
	<div class="modal-dialog">
		<div class="modal-content">
			<div class="modal-header">
				<button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal"><span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span><span class="sr-only">Close</span></button>
				<h4 class="modal-title" id="myModalLabel">What is Neighborly?</h4>
			</div>
			<div class="modal-body">
				Neighborly aims to bring communities together by finding the best places to eat, drink, and meet people in real time.
				Enter in a neighborhood by name, and we'll give you the most hopping places to be;
				from there, feel free to filter by specifics and view other peoples photos who have been in the area.
				Logging in with twitter gives the ability to upload photos yourself, and save your favorite neighborhoods for quick access.
				Party on.
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>
